    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "@Haroenv - As per your sandbox \"**https://xo94wl403z.csb.app/**\" is your base URL so, if I want to redirect the user to another page after clicking on hit i.e \"**Amazon - Fire TV Stick with Alexa Voice Remote - Black**\". At that time whatever the URL of that hit is, it gets appended to the base URL \r\nfor example:-\r\n\r\nIf my URL for that hit (specific entity) is:-  \"https://codesandbox.io\"\r\n\r\nOnce I click on that hit, Url gets appended to the base URL \r\nhttps://xo94wl403z.csb.app/https://codesandbox.io\r\nlike this.\r\n\r\nI just don't want that to happen.\r\n\r\n**NOTE:- This Happens when i use template in another file like,**\r\n\r\nI have created \r\n\r\n```\r\n<script type=\"text/html\" id=\"hit-template-row\">\r\n<div id=\"hit-template-row\">\r\n      <article>\r\n        <a href=\"https://www.algolia.com/users/sign_in\">{{#helpers.highlight}}{ \"attribute\": \"name\" }{{/helpers.highlight}}</a>\r\n        <p>{{#helpers.highlight}}{ \"attribute\": \"description\" }{{/helpers.highlight}}</p>\r\n      </article>\r\n</script>\r\n```\r\nAnd geting this template using \r\n\r\n\r\n```\r\nitem :document.getElementById('hit-template-row').innerHTML\r\n```",
